#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:1
msgid "VTK::RenderingOpenXR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:3
msgid ""
"The `OpenXR` module aims to support rendering to a variety of mixed reality "
"devices under the OpenXR industry-wide standard. Detailed information on the "
"OpenXR specification and compliant OpenXR runtimes may be found on the "
"[Khronos Group website](https://www.khronos.org/openxr/)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:8
msgid "Supported Devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:10
msgid ""
"The OpenXR standard is implemented by most PC-based OpenXR runtimes and "
"devices. The VTK `OpenXR` module aims to support most devices that implement "
"the OpenXR specification and support OpenGL rendering."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:14
msgid ""
"The list of possible XR device targets is extensive and constantly "
"expanding. At the time of writing, theoretically supported devices include "
"but are not limited to the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:17
msgid "Valve Index"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:18
msgid "HTC Vive (, Pro)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:19
msgid "Meta Quest (1,2,3,Pro)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:20
msgid ""
"[Quest Link](https://www.meta.com/help/quest/articles/headsets-and-"
"accessories/oculus-link/connect-link-with-quest-2/) or [Air Link](https://"
"www.meta.com/help/quest/articles/headsets-and-accessories/oculus-link/"
"connect-with-air-link/) only"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:21
msgid "HP Reverb G2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:23
msgid "Supported input devices and mechanisms include the following:"
msgstr ""

