"Rendering/OpenXR/vtk_openxr_binding_oculus_touch_controller.json)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:29
msgid ""
"Valve Knuckles [json](https://gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk/-/blob/master/"
"Rendering/OpenXR/vtk_openxr_binding_knuckles.json)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:31
msgid ""
"The `OpenXR` module is commonly tested with the Valve Index and HTC Vive "
"virtual reality headsets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:34
msgid "Adding New Devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:36
msgid ""
"It may be necessary to tell VTK how to handle inputs from a new OpenXR-"
"compatible device. Consider contributing a new JSON input binding "
"specification to add support for a new XR device to the VTK `OpenXR` module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:40
msgid "The OpenXR interaction profile specification is documented here:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:42
msgid ""
"https://registry.khronos.org/OpenXR/specs/1.0/html/xrspec.html#semantic-path-"
"interaction-profiles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:44
msgid ""
"Input binding JSON files should be added to `OpenXR` and set as default in "
"`vtk_openxr_actions.json`[json](https://gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk/-/blob/"
"master/Rendering/OpenXR/vtk_openxr_actions.json)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:47
msgid "Building"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:49
msgid ""
"The `OpenXR` module depends on the [`OpenXR-SDK`](https://github.com/"
"KhronosGroup/OpenXR-SDK) library. `OpenXR-SDK` can be built with CMake via "
"the steps below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:52
msgid ""
"> git clone git@github.com:KhronosGroup/OpenXR-SDK.git\n"
"> mkdir OpenXR-SDK-build\n"
"> cd OpenXR-SDK-build\n"
"OpenXR-SDK-build > cmake ../OpenXR-SDK\n"
"OpenXR-SDK-build > cmake --build . --config \"Release\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:60
msgid ""
"The `OpenXR` is turned off in VTK by default. Run the following steps to "
"build VTK with OpenXR:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:62
msgid ""
"VTK-build > cmake -DVTK_MODULE_ENABLE_VTK_RenderingOpenXR:STRING=YES -"
"DOpenXR_INCLUDE_DIR:PATH=\"path/to/OpenXR-SDK/include/openxr\" -"
"DOpenXR_LIBRARY:FILEPATH=\"path/to/OpenXR-SDK-build/src/loader/Release/"
"openxr_loader.lib\" path/to/VTK\n"
"VTK-build > cmake --build . --config \"Release\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:67
msgid "Controller Model Rendering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:69
msgid ""
"OpenXR does not yet provide any api for rendering controller models in the "
"same way that OpenVR does, though work towards that goal has been in "
"progress for a long time.  Until that materializes, VTK provides a way to "
"render glTF controller models by using the currently active interaction "
"profile to index into a customizable lookup table of rendering assets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:71
msgid ""
"Out of the box, VTK does not come with any controller models for the `VTK::"
"RenderingOpenXR` module to render, but a data archive containing models for "
"a subset of the currently supported interaction profiles is available from "
"[here](https://www.paraview.org/files/data/OpenXRControllerModels-0.1.tgz).  "
"Those models are included by default in ParaView binary downloads, but can "
"be extracted into any build or install tree, and VTK will automatically find "
"and use them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:73
msgid ""
"Though some of the contents are omitted below for expository purposes, the "
"structure of the default model archive is mostly as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:75
msgid ""
"OpenXRControllerModels-<version>/\n"
"OpenXRControllerModels-<version>/openxr_controllermodels.json\n"
"OpenXRControllerModels-<version>/valve_index/\n"
"OpenXRControllerModels-<version>/valve_index/left/\n"
"OpenXRControllerModels-<version>/valve_index/left/scene.gltf\n"
"OpenXRControllerModels-<version>/valve_index/right/\n"
"OpenXRControllerModels-<version>/valve_index/right/scene.gltf\n"
"OpenXRControllerModels-<version>/htc_vive/\n"
"OpenXRControllerModels-<version>/htc_vive/scene.gltf\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:87
msgid ""
"Models are also accompanied by a binary file containing geometry, a base "
"color image, and a license file detailing model attribution and the terms "
"under which the model is distributed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:89
msgid "The contents of `openxr_controllermodels.json` looks like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:91
msgid ""
"[\n"
"  {\n"
"    \"interaction_profile\": \"/interaction_profiles/htc/vive_controller\",\n"
"    \"asset_paths\": {\n"
"      \"left_controller\": \"htc_vive/scene.gltf\",\n"
"      \"right_controller\": \"htc_vive/scene.gltf\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  },\n"
"  {\n"
"    \"interaction_profile\": \"/interaction_profiles/valve/"
"index_controller\",\n"
"    \"asset_paths\": {\n"
"      \"left_controller\": \"valve_index/left/scene.gltf\",\n"
"      \"right_controller\": \"valve_index/right/scene.gltf\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:110
msgid ""
"Note it's just a json array of objects. Each object contains an interaction "
"profile, which should match one of those referenced in the binding files "
"found in `VTK/Rendering/OpenxR/` or `ParaView/Plugins/XRInterface/Plugin/`. "
"Each object also contains a dictionary indicating relative path (from the "
"root of the model archive) to glTF models for left and right controllers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:112
msgid ""
"By extracting this archive (or a sufficiently similar one) into your VTK or "
"ParaView build or install tree, the `VTK::RenderingOpenXR` module will be "
"able to render the supplied models in place of the default green pyramids. "
"Note that downloaded ParaView binaries come with this default set of "
"controller models already installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:114
msgid "Testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:116
msgid ""
"Minimum OpenXR examples are available in the [`Testing/Cxx`](https://gitlab."
"kitware.com/vtk/vtk/-/blob/master/Rendering/OpenXR/Testing/Cxx) directory "
"for testing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:118
msgid "To run OpenXR tests, first build VTK with testing enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:120
msgid ""
"VTK-build > cmake -DVTK_BUILD_TESTING:BOOL=ON path/to/VTK\n"
"VTK-build > cmake --build . --config \"Release\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:125
msgid "Then run the test with CTest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:127
msgid "VTK-build > ctest -C Release -R <name_of_test>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:131
msgid "Additional Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:133
msgid ""
"See [VTK `OpenXRRemoting` documentation](../OpenXRRemoting/README.md) for "
"information on virtual reality rendering to DirectX devices such as the "
"Microsoft HoloLens 2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/OpenXR/README.md:136
msgid ""
"Some non-OpenGL devices may be compatible with the WebGL and WebXR "
"specifications. If your XR device does not support OpenGL or OpenXR, we "
"suggest visiting [VTK.js WebXR documentation](https://kitware.github.io/vtk-"
"js/docs/develop_webxr.html) for a web-driven solution."
msgstr ""
